The City of Joburgâ€™s Environment and Infrastructure Services Department (EISD) has been closed! This is after one of the employees died due to covid-19. The spokesman of EISD, Stan Itshegetseng told Daily Sun that the employee was being treated at the hospital. "On Friday afternoon, we discovered that the employee has succumbed to this pandemic. May his Soul Rest in Eternal Peace," said Itshegetseng. He also said those who had direct contact with the deceased have been informed and are currently self isolating, monitoring their symptoms and in the process of undergoing testing. "The building will be closed for deep cleaning and sanitizing, and will be reopened on Thursday, the 9th of July," he said. Itshegetseng is urging all employees to adhere to the health protocols as provided by the health team regarding the Covid-19 safety precautions, to maintain social distancing, wear face masks at all times, wash hands with soap and water or alternatively use sanitizers.